OL,3,C'Scandal waiting to happen': One in 9
OL,4,Cnew homes built in flood risk areas
OL,6,FFormer Environment Agency chairwoman,
OL,7,Fand now chairwoman of ClientEarth and
OL,8,Fthe London Climate Resilience Review,
OL,9,FEmma Howard Boyd, warned building
OL,10,Fhouses that would flood was "a future
OL,11,Fscandal waiting to happen".
OL,13,FAviva also warns that the new homes
OL,14,Fbeing built in flood risk areas are
OL,15,Fnot eligible for the Flood Re scheme
OL,16,Fto make insurance affordable and
OL,17,Faccessible for households living in
OL,18,Fhigh-risk areas.
